<section xml:id="subsec-dictionaries">
    <title>Dictionaries</title>
    
    <p>
        We can refer to an element in a list by its index. Sometimes, though, we might want to reference
        things in a different way. A dictionary pairs a key with an element.
    </p>

    <p>
        For example,

        <sage language="python">
            <input>
               my_pet = {'name':'Max', 'species':'dog', 'personality':'needy'}
               
               print(my_pet['name'])
               print(f"My pet {my_pet['species']} is named {my_pet['name']} and is very {my_pet['personality']}.")
            </input>
        </sage>
    </p>

    <p>
        As another example,
        <sage language="python">
            <input>
                person = {
                    'name': 'Alice',
                    'age': 30,
                    'is_student': False
                }

                person['age'] = 31
person['email'] = 'alice@example.com'

print(person.keys())
print(person.values())
print(person.items())
                
            </input>
        </sage>
    </p>

